moves.name: Light Screen
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from special attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, special damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Reflect
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user and its party members take 0.5x damage from physical attacks, or 0.66x damage if in a Double Battle. Damage is not reduced further with Aurora Veil. Critical hits ignore this effect. It is removed from the user's side if the user or an ally is successfully hit by Brick Break, Psychic Fangs, or Defog. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Light Clay. Fails if the effect is already active on the user's side.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, physical damage to allies is halved.

moves.name: Dazzling Gleam
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect. Hits adjacent foes.

moves.name: Thunder Wave
moves.desc: Paralyzes the target. This move does not ignore type immunity.
moves.shortDesc: Paralyzes the target.

moves.name: Trick Room
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the Speed of every Pokemon is recalculated for the purposes of determining turn order. During the effect, each Pokemon's Speed is considered to be (10000 - its normal Speed), and if this value is greater than 8191, 8192 is subtracted from it. If this move is used during the effect, the effect ends.
moves.shortDesc: Goes last. For 5 turns, turn order is reversed.

moves.name: Sandstorm
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sandstorm. At the end of each turn except the last, all active Pokemon lose 1/16 of their maximum HP, rounded down, unless they are a Ground, Rock, or Steel type, or have the Magic Guard, Overcoat, Sand Force, Sand Rush, or Sand Veil Abilities. During the effect, the Special Defense of Rock-type Pokemon is multiplied by 1.5 when taking damage from a special attack. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Smooth Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sandstorm.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, a sandstorm rages. Rock: 1.5x SpD.

moves.name: Misty Terrain
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the terrain becomes Misty Terrain. During the effect, the power of Dragon-type attacks used against grounded Pokemon is multiplied by 0.5 and grounded Pokemon cannot be inflicted with a non-volatile status condition nor confusion. Grounded Pokemon can become affected by Yawn but cannot fall asleep from its effect. Camouflage transforms the user into a Fairy type, Nature Power becomes Moonblast, and Secret Power has a 30% chance to lower Special Attack by 1 stage. Fails if the current terrain is Misty Terrain.
moves.shortDesc: 5 turns. Can't status,-Dragon power vs grounded.

moves.name: Draining Kiss
moves.desc: The user recovers 3/4 the HP lost by the target, rounded half up. If Big Root is held by the user, the HP recovered is 1.3x normal, rounded half down.
moves.shortDesc: User recovers 75% of the damage dealt.

moves.name: Spikes
moves.desc: Sets up a hazard on the opposing side of the field, damaging each opposing Pokemon that switches in, unless it is a Flying-type Pokemon or has the Levitate Ability. Can be used up to three times before failing. Opponents lose 1/8 of their maximum HP with one layer, 1/6 of their maximum HP with two layers, and 1/4 of their maximum HP with three layers, all rounded down. Can be removed from the opposing side if any opposing Pokemon uses Mortal Spin, Rapid Spin, or Defog successfully, or is hit by Defog.
moves.shortDesc: Hurts grounded foes on switch-in. Max 3 layers.

moves.name: Rain Dance
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Rain Dance. The damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Damp Rock. Fails if the current weather is Rain Dance.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, heavy rain powers Water moves.

moves.name: Foul Play
moves.desc: Damage is calculated using the target's Attack stat, including stat stage changes. The user's Ability, item, and burn are used as normal.
moves.shortDesc: Uses target's Attack stat in damage calculation.

moves.name: Psych Up
moves.desc: The user copies all of the target's current stat stage changes.
moves.shortDesc: Copies the target's current stat stages.

moves.name: Stored Power
moves.desc: Power is equal to 20+(X*20), where X is the user's total stat stage changes that are greater than 0.
moves.shortDesc: + 20 power for each of the user's stat boosts.

moves.name: Steel Beam
moves.desc: Whether or not this move is successful and even if it would cause fainting, the user loses 1/2 of its maximum HP, rounded up, unless the user has the Magic Guard Ability.
moves.shortDesc: User loses 50% max HP.

moves.name: Protect
moves.desc: The user is protected from most attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents moves from affecting the user this turn.

moves.name: Metal Sound
moves.desc: Lowers the target's Special Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Lowers the target's Sp. Def by 2.

moves.name: Calm Mind
moves.desc: Raises the user's Special Attack and Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Sp. Atk and Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Recycle
moves.desc: The user regains the item it last used. Fails if the user is holding an item, if the user has not held an item, if the item was a popped Air Balloon, if the item was picked up by a Pokemon with the Pickup Ability, or if the item was lost to Bug Bite, Corrosive Gas, Covet, Incinerate, Knock Off, Pluck, or Thief. Items thrown with Fling can be regained.
moves.shortDesc: Restores the item the user last used.

moves.name: Flash Cannon
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Switcheroo
moves.desc: The user swaps its held item with the target's held item. Fails if either the user or the target is holding a Mail or Z-Crystal, if neither is holding an item, if the user is trying to give or take a Mega Stone to or from the species that can Mega Evolve with it, or if the user is trying to give or take a Blue Orb, a Red Orb, a Griseous Orb, a Plate, a Drive, or a Memory to or from a Kyogre, a Groudon, a Giratina, an Arceus, a Genesect, or a Silvally, respectively. The target is immune to this move if it has the Sticky Hold Ability.
moves.shortDesc: User switches its held item with the target's.

moves.name: Sunny Day
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the weather becomes Sunny Day. The damage of Fire-type attacks is multiplied by 1.5 and the damage of Water-type attacks is multiplied by 0.5 during the effect. Lasts for 8 turns if the user is holding Heat Rock. Fails if the current weather is Sunny Day.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, intense sunlight powers Fire moves.

moves.name: Magnet Rise
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the user is immune to Ground-type attacks and the effects of Spikes, Toxic Spikes, Sticky Web, and the Arena Trap Ability as long as it remains active. If the user uses Baton Pass, the replacement will gain the effect. Ingrain, Smack Down, Thousand Arrows, and Iron Ball override this move if the user is under any of their effects. Fails if the user is already under this effect or the effects of Ingrain, Smack Down, or Thousand Arrows.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, the user has immunity to Ground.

moves.name: Play Rough
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Attack by 1.

moves.name: Psychic
moves.desc: Has a 10% chance to lower the target's Special Defense by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 10% chance to lower the target's Sp. Def by 1.

moves.name: Iron Defense
moves.desc: Raises the user's Defense by 2 stages.
moves.shortDesc: Raises the user's Defense by 2.

moves.name: Magic Room
moves.desc: For 5 turns, the held items of all active Pokemon have no effect. An item's effect of causing forme changes is unaffected, but any other effects from such items are negated. During the effect, Fling and Natural Gift are prevented from being used by all active Pokemon. If this move is used during the effect, the effect ends.
moves.shortDesc: For 5 turns, all held items have no effect.

moves.name: Fairy Lock
moves.desc: Prevents all active Pokemon from switching next turn. A Pokemon can still switch out if it is holding Shed Shell or uses Baton Pass, Flip Turn, Parting Shot, Teleport, U-turn, or Volt Switch. Fails if the effect is already active.
moves.shortDesc: Prevents all Pokemon from switching next turn.

moves.name: Fairy Wind
moves.desc: No additional effect.
moves.shortDesc: No additional effect.

moves.name: Torment
moves.desc: Prevents the target from selecting the same move for use two turns in a row. This effect ends when the target is no longer active.
moves.shortDesc: Target can't select the same move twice in a row.

moves.name: Tera Blast
moves.desc: If the user is Terastallized, this move becomes a physical attack if the user's Attack is greater than its Special Attack, including stat stage changes, and this move's type becomes the same as the user's Tera Type. In addition, if the user's Tera Type is Stellar, this move has 100 power, is super effective against Terastallized targets and neutral against other targets, and lowers the user's Attack and Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: If Terastallized: Phys. if Atk > SpA, type = Tera.

moves.name: Last Resort
moves.desc: This move fails unless the user knows this move and at least one other move, and has used all the other moves it knows at least once each since it became active or Transformed.
moves.shortDesc: Fails unless each known move has been used.

moves.name: Rest
moves.desc: The user falls asleep for the next two turns and restores all of its HP, curing itself of any non-volatile status condition in the process. Fails if the user has full HP, is already asleep, or if another effect is preventing sleep.
moves.shortDesc: User sleeps 2 turns and restores HP and status.

moves.name: Sleep Talk
moves.desc: One of the user's known moves, besides this move, is selected for use at random. Fails if the user is not asleep. The selected move does not have PP deducted from it, and can currently have 0 PP. This move cannot select Assist, Beak Blast, Belch, Bide, Blazing Torque, Celebrate, Chatter, Combat Torque, Copycat, Dynamax Cannon, Focus Punch, Hold Hands, Magical Torque, Me First, Metronome, Mimic, Mirror Move, Nature Power, Noxious Torque, Shell Trap, Sketch, Sleep Talk, Struggle, Uproar, Wicked Torque, or any two-turn move.
moves.shortDesc: User must be asleep. Uses another known move.

moves.name: Skitter Smack
moves.desc: Has a 100% chance to lower the target's Special Attack by 1 stage.
moves.shortDesc: 100% chance to lower target's Sp. Atk by 1.

moves.name: Substitute
moves.desc: The user takes 1/4 of its maximum HP, rounded down, and puts it into a substitute to take its place in battle. The substitute is removed once enough damage is inflicted on it, or if the user switches out or faints. Baton Pass can be used to transfer the substitute to an ally, and the substitute will keep its remaining HP. Until the substitute is broken, it receives damage from all attacks made by other Pokemon and shields the user from status effects and stat stage changes caused by other Pokemon. Sound-based moves and Pokemon with the Infiltrator Ability ignore substitutes. The user still takes normal damage from weather and status effects while behind its substitute. If the substitute breaks during a multi-hit attack, the user will take damage from any remaining hits. If a substitute is created while the user is trapped by a binding move, the binding effect ends immediately. Fails if the user does not have enough HP remaining to create a substitute without fainting, or if it already has a substitute.
moves.shortDesc: User takes 1/4 its max HP to put in a substitute.

moves.name: Thief
moves.desc: If this attack was successful and the user has not fainted, it steals the target's held item if the user is not holding one. The target's item is not stolen if it is a Mail or Z-Crystal, or if the target is a Kyogre holding a Blue Orb, a Groudon holding a Red Orb, a Giratina holding a Griseous Orb, an Arceus holding a Plate, a Genesect holding a Drive, a Silvally holding a Memory, or a Pokemon that can Mega Evolve holding the Mega Stone for its species. Items lost to this move cannot be regained with Recycle or the Harvest Ability.
moves.shortDesc: If the user has no item, it steals the target's.

moves.name: Endure
moves.desc: The user will survive attacks made by other Pokemon during this turn with at least 1 HP. This move has a 1/X chance of being successful, where X starts at 1 and triples each time this move is successfully used. X resets to 1 if this move fails, if the user's last move used is not Baneful Bunker, Burning Bulwark, Detect, Endure, King's Shield, Max Guard, Obstruct, Protect, Quick Guard, Silk Trap, Spiky Shield, or Wide Guard, or if it was one of those moves and the user's protection was broken. Fails if the user moves last this turn.
moves.shortDesc: User survives attacks this turn with at least 1 HP.

moves.name: Psyshock
moves.desc: Deals damage to the target based on its Defense instead of Special Defense.
moves.shortDesc: Damages target based on Defense, not Sp. Def.

abilities.name: Prankster
abilities.desc: This Pokemon's non-damaging moves have their priority increased by 1. Opposing Dark-type Pokemon are immune to these moves, and any move called by these moves, if the resulting user of the move has this Ability.
abilities.shortDesc: This Pokemon's Status moves have priority raised by 1, but Dark types are immune.

abilities.name: Magician
abilities.desc: If this Pokemon has no item, it steals the item off a Pokemon it hits with an attack. Does not affect Doom Desire and Future Sight.
abilities.shortDesc: If this Pokemon has no item, it steals the item off a Pokemon it hits with an attack.

items.name: Light Clay
items.desc: Holder's use of Aurora Veil, Light Screen, or Reflect lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Mental Herb
items.desc: Cures holder of Attract, Disable, Encore, Heal Block, Taunt, Torment. Single use.

items.name: Sitrus Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/4 max HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Leftovers
items.desc: At the end of every turn, holder restores 1/16 of its max HP.

items.name: Covert Cloak
items.desc: Holder is not affected by the secondary effect of another Pokemon's attack.

items.name: Damp Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Rain Dance lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Rocky Helmet
items.desc: If holder is hit by a contact move, the attacker loses 1/6 of its max HP.

items.name: Occa Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Fire-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Iron Ball
items.desc: Holder is grounded, Speed halved. If Flying type, takes neutral Ground damage.

items.name: Smooth Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Sandstorm lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Grassy Seed
items.desc: If the terrain is Grassy Terrain, raises holder's Defense by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Air Balloon
items.desc: Holder is immune to Ground-type attacks. Pops when holder is hit.

items.name: Red Card
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, attacker is forced to switch to a random ally. Single use.

items.name: Lum Berry
items.desc: Holder cures itself if it has a non-volatile status or is confused. Single use.

items.name: Eject Button
items.desc: If holder survives a hit, it immediately switches out to a chosen ally. Single use.

items.name: Shuca Berry
items.desc: Halves damage taken from a supereffective Ground-type attack. Single use.

items.name: Focus Sash
items.desc: If holder's HP is full, will survive an attack that would KO it with 1 HP. Single use.

items.name: Lagging Tail
items.desc: Holder moves last in its priority bracket.

items.name: Flame Orb
items.desc: At the end of every turn, this item attempts to burn the holder.

items.name: Toxic Orb
items.desc: At the end of every turn, this item attempts to badly poison the holder.

items.name: Bright Powder
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks against the holder is 0.9x.

items.name: Heat Rock
items.desc: Holder's use of Sunny Day lasts 8 turns instead of 5.

items.name: Aguav Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpD Nature. Single use.

items.name: Heavy-Duty Boots
items.desc: When switching in, the holder is unaffected by hazards on its side of the field.

items.name: Figy Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Atk Nature. Single use.

items.name: Safety Goggles
items.desc: Holder is immune to powder moves and damage from Sandstorm or Hail.

items.name: Choice Scarf
items.desc: Holder's Speed is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Life Orb
items.desc: Holder's attacks do 1.3x damage, and it loses 1/10 its max HP after the attack.

items.name: Mago Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Spe Nature. Single use.

items.name: Choice Specs
items.desc: Holder's Sp. Atk is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Iapapa Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -Def Nature. Single use.

items.name: Sticky Barb
items.desc: Each turn, holder loses 1/8 max HP. An attacker making contact can receive it.

items.name: Room Service
items.desc: If Trick Room is active, the holder's Speed is lowered by 1 stage. Single use.

items.name: Wellspring Mask
items.desc: Ogerpon-Wellspring: 1.2x power attacks; Terastallize to gain Embody Aspect.

items.name: Wide Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.1x.

items.name: Wiki Berry
items.desc: Restores 1/3 max HP at 1/4 max HP or less; confuses if -SpA Nature. Single use.

items.name: Ability Shield
items.desc: Holder's Ability cannot be changed by any effect.

items.name: Ring Target
items.desc: The holder's type immunities granted solely by its typing are negated.

items.name: Silk Scarf
items.desc: Holder's Normal-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Metal Coat
items.desc: Holder's Steel-type attacks have 1.2x power. Evolves Onix into Steelix and Scyther into Scizor when traded.

items.name: Eviolite
items.desc: If holder's species can evolve, its Defense and Sp. Def are 1.5x.

items.name: White Herb
items.desc: Restores all lowered stat stages to 0 when one is less than 0. Single use.

items.name: Jaboca Berry
items.desc: If holder is hit by a physical move, attacker loses 1/8 of its max HP. Single use.

items.name: Shell Bell
items.desc: After an attack, holder gains 1/8 of the damage in HP dealt to other Pokemon.

items.name: Choice Band
items.desc: Holder's Attack is 1.5x, but it can only select the first move it executes.

items.name: Oran Berry
items.desc: Restores 10 HP when at 1/2 max HP or less. Single use.

items.name: Chesto Berry
items.desc: Holder wakes up if it is asleep. Single use.

items.name: Zoom Lens
items.desc: The accuracy of attacks by the holder is 1.2x if it moves after its target.

items.name: Weakness Policy
items.desc: If holder is hit super effectively, raises Attack, Sp. Atk by 2 stages. Single use.

items.name: Iron Plate
items.desc: Holder's Steel-type attacks have 1.2x power. Judgment is Steel type.

items.name: Big Root
items.desc: Holder gains 1.3x HP from draining/Aqua Ring/Ingrain/Leech Seed/Strength Sap.

items.name: Metronome
items.desc: Damage of moves used on consecutive turns is increased. Max 2x after 5 turns.

items.name: Fairy Feather
items.desc: Holder's Fairy-type attacks have 1.2x power.

items.name: Custap Berry
items.desc: Holder moves first in its priority bracket when at 1/4 max HP or less. Single use.
